Problem Statement:
Create a responsive online bookstore homepage that demonstrates the use of HTML elements, CSS styling,
Flexbox, Grid, and media queries.
Requirements:
1. Design the following sections:
✓ Header with bookstore logo and navigation menu
✓ Hero banner
✓ Book Categories
✓ Featured Books (minimum six book cards)
✓ Customer Reviews
✓ Contact Form
✓ Footer
2. Use HTML elements including:
✓ Headings and paragraphs
✓ Hyperlinks
✓ Ordered and unordered lists
✓ Images
✓ Tables displaying book details (Title, Author, Price, Rating)
✓ Forms with appropriate input fields
3. Apply CSS for:
✓ Typography, colors, spacing, and backgrounds
✓ Hover effects on buttons and navigation links
✓ Card styling for books and reviews
4. Use:
✓ CSS Flexbox for the navigation bar and footer.
✓ CSS Grid for arranging the featured book cards.
5. Implement responsive layouts using media queries for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.
Deliverables:
✓ index.html
✓ style.css
✓ Screenshots of the webpage in desktop, tablet, and mobile views.
Learning Outcomes:
✓ Create structured web pages using HTML5.
✓ Apply CSS styling techniques.
✓ Develop responsive layouts using Flexbox, Grid, and media queries